Survey_Notes: no cuckoo detected but ID's YBCH, PHPE, SUTA, BEVI, COBH, GBHE, CAWR, flycatchers and woodpeckers. Trees on verde are young and mostly willow, ash and sycamore. Most cottonwoods are in Gap creek along the trail
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Survey_Notes: 0 YBCU observed. monsoons circling the area, very humid!
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Detection_Notes: YBCU #1 female coo
YBCU #2 contact response to female

detection occured at waypoint #1. she never responded during the 5 minute survey, but she cooed after about 7 minutes of us being there. We did spot a loose stick nest in a cottonwood tree near to where we heard the YBCU.

Survey_Notes: no YBCU detected, low bird activity overall, very breezy and trees were somewhat noisy
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Survey_Notes: no YBCU detected, but lots of songbird activity. Coopers hawk juvie at second to last point. No standing water, but lots of gnats. Flycathcers, bells vireo, yello-breasted chat, gambels quail, hummingbird, cardinal, pheno pepla
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Survey_Notes: 358266, 3806429 original start --> didn't call saw 3 raptors

SurveyPt_Notes: COHA between waypoints 4 + 5 --> move 300 from COHA
COHA between waypoints 4 + 5 --> move 300 from COHA

Detection_Notes: silent fly in to desert willow
Survey_Notes: suspect the detections could be one single YBCU. Followed protocol and moved 300m before calling again at a lower volume.

Detection_Notes: flew in from cottonwood and down drainage
flew in from cottonwood near road

Survey_Notes: cows present in site at 355908, 3801677 (x5)
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Survey_Notes: 0 YBCU detected. Roadrunner calling at windmill (start) and RTHA juvie present for most of survey. conducted route in reverse from "normal"/previous surveys
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH
Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Detection_Notes: YBCU detection #2 is the same bird calling from the same location (cottonwood @ UTM 356206, 3802505 exactly). Due to the openness of landscape, I continued to hear this bird for ~1000m, it did follow for a whilem despite traveling 300+ mters and trying to broadcast away and more quietly each time.
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Survey_Notes: no YBCU detected. common black hawk flewe in on the last call point duirng the first broadcast. We discontinued broadcasting and silently listened for the remaining time. There were not many flying insects on the call route, even next to the still sections of river. Not "buggy" overall.
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Detection_Notes: came from private property
Survey_Notes: coopers hawk @ 388969, 3861975 so we did not broadcast at that point.
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Detection_Notes: incidental detection immediately when getting out of truck. individual cooing approximately at 389884, 3862149 in cottonwood trees. location is ~400m from beginning of route, so i continued upstream from this location for survey.
Survey_Notes: coopers hawk @ end of route
Comments: Negative detection data was not recorded - GH

Detection_Notes: unconfident visual ID of YBCU @ waypoint 10. Flew in and  out of area quickly, could be ATEC

contact response to female
